commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: Ib309507e9982e34cde1de5624587d9f0605bbde3
Story: #2002586
Task: #24341

subject: Add script for tests deletion from builded project
reviewers: [{'_account_id': 6507, 'name': 'Shturm Svetlana', 'email': 'svetlana.v.shturm@gmail.com', 'username': 'sshturm'}, {'_account_id': 14119, 'name': 'Sam Yaple', 'email': 'sam+git@yaple.net', 'username': 'SamYaple'}, {'_account_id': 17068, 'name': 'Jean-Philippe Evrard', 'email': 'openstack@a.spamming.party', 'username': 'evrardjp'}, {'_account_id': 22348, 'name': 'Zuul', 'username': 'zuul', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 23928, 'name': 'Pete Birley', 'email': 'petebirley@gmail.com', 'username': 'portdirect'}, {'_account_id': 24049, 'name': 'Pete Birley', 'inactive': True}, {'_account_id': 25731, 'name': 'Stacey Fletcher', 'email': 'staceylynnfletcher@gmail.com', 'username': 'StaceyFletcher'}, {'_account_id': 26628, 'name': 'Kaspars Skels', 'email': 'kaspars.skels@att.com', 'username': 'kskels'}]
messages:
[{'account_id': 6507, 'date': '2018-08-01 19:35:48.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 23928, 'date': '2018-08-01 19:55:47.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

If you desire this functionality, why not remove from the repo prior to building?'}, {'account_id': 6507, 'date': '2018-08-01 21:05:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

@Pete
Project folder has to be cloned by separate script clone_project.sh in loci repo from remote repo by git clone command. We can not remove tests folder from project repo because review job for this repo executes tox checks that are based on tests folder.
We can just remove it during loci build.'}, {'account_id': 23928, 'date': '2018-08-01 21:33:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

> @Pete
 > Project folder has to be cloned by separate script clone_project.sh
 > in loci repo from remote repo by git clone command. We can not
 > remove tests folder from project repo because review job for this
 > repo executes tox checks that are based on tests folder.
 > We can just remove it during loci build.

In this file, you are cloning the repo, and then serving locally: https://review.gerrithub.io/#/c/att-comdev/cicd/+/417936/24/images/openstack/loci/JenkinsfileMos, it would be trivial to add this sanitization as a step there.'}, {'account_id': 6507, 'date': '2018-08-01 22:55:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

@Pete
This code just initiate repo without cloning source code itself.
The project source will be cloned as a part of command "${DIND} docker build --force-rm --no-cache ${LOCI_REPO} ${DEFAULT_ARGS} ${projConfArgs} ${wheelArgs} ${labels} --tag ${image_tag}".
This command will use internal script install.sh from loci repo that contains separate step for clone repo.
I still not see another best place to patch project repo only this one.'}, {'account_id': 14119, 'date': '2018-08-02 16:17:17.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I don't understand the issue this is solving.

Can you describe what is breaking for you?"}, {'account_id': 6507, 'date': '2018-08-02 16:41:28.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

@Sam
We have a requirement to build container for openstack component without tests folder. So all security checks against this image will be failed only on relevant things.
Adding just this script alone into this repo will not solve the problem.
We also need to add this script execution after clone_project.sh in install.sh
For now we are patching install.sh after repo loci is cloned.'}, {'account_id': 14119, 'date': '2018-08-02 17:59:59.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

> @Sam
 > We have a requirement to build container for openstack component
 > without tests folder. So all security checks against this image
 > will be failed only on relevant things.
 > Adding just this script alone into this repo will not solve the
 > problem.
 > We also need to add this script execution after clone_project.sh in
 > install.sh
 > For now we are patching install.sh after repo loci is cloned.

Something like this is unlikely to get merged into LOCI upstream. It is pretty specific to your needs and doesn't sound useful otherwise.

Anything that modifies the contents of the git repo should be done *before* starting to build the LOCI image. You can fork horizon and remove the tests, then feed that fork to LOCI to build without modifying LOCI."}, {'account_id': 17068, 'date': '2018-08-09 09:56:08.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

> > @Sam
 > > We have a requirement to build container for openstack component
 > > without tests folder. So all security checks against this image
 > > will be failed only on relevant things.
 > > Adding just this script alone into this repo will not solve the
 > > problem.
 > > We also need to add this script execution after clone_project.sh
 > in
 > > install.sh
 > > For now we are patching install.sh after repo loci is cloned.
 > 
 > Something like this is unlikely to get merged into LOCI upstream.
 > It is pretty specific to your needs and doesn't sound useful
 > otherwise.
 > 
 > Anything that modifies the contents of the git repo should be done
 > *before* starting to build the LOCI image. You can fork horizon and
 > remove the tests, then feed that fork to LOCI to build without
 > modifying LOCI.

Agreed, I see no point of bringing this in. And on top of it, the commit message would not be explicit enough here."}, {'account_id': 26628, 'date': '2018-08-23 15:41:44.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Is there a reason we would like to keep tests as part of LOCI container image that is being built?

By removing tests we are making image leaner, and potentially removing unnecessary packages?'}, {'account_id': 14119, 'date': '2018-08-23 18:28:01.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

> Is there a reason we would like to keep tests as part of LOCI
 > container image that is being built?
 > 
 > By removing tests we are making image leaner, and potentially
 > removing unnecessary packages?

Our goal is not to modify the projects we are building, but work with what they give us. Towards that end, the solution you are proposing (do not install tests) should be proposed to those projects.

However, thats just for this code base. You can modify anything you want to install before you feed it to LOCI and you can know that LOCI won't be undoing any of your changes by doing things like removing the 'tests' folders"}, {'account_id': 26628, 'date': '2018-08-23 20:41:43.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

Thanks Sam! I agree.'}, {'account_id': 6507, 'date': '2018-08-24 15:11:13.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Make divisibility py3 compatible in DRBD driver

In python 2.x,
int / int = int
Eg: 3 / 2 = 1

But in python 3.x,
int / int = float (if the result turns out to be a
floating value)
Eg: 3 / 2 = 1.5

This patch addresses the change.

Change-Id: Ifa63b1b14bd9457ff0f76e729e3c1fd2ecdaee04

Fixing anti-affinity for Sahara

Sahara anti-affinity was broken since some problematic changes in
cd1569852614698c4843d4c97475d8f8f3069478.

This should be able to fix it.

commit_message:
Add openstacksdk to installed packages

In order to continue CI testing of openstacksdk
and related interactions with shade while functionality
is transitioned from shade to openstacksdk, we must install
openstacksdk first.

Andreas, in the section: https://docs.openstack.org/infra/manual/creators.html#adding-the-project-to-the-ci-system

It says that "you need two separate changes to setup your new project" ... and goes on to describe what I originally did. commit_message:
Import statement removed on core.py

from charms_openstack.charm import defaults was removed
to allow Trusty's python 3.4 to run.
Two variables that were present on defaults.py were
migrated to core.py to allow removal.

Change-Id: I90d3aae867a21417b701e0fd40a75a57d827eb52
Closes-Bug: #1788610

[{'created': '2018-08-23 13:02:38.000000000', 'message': 'Consider prereleases when working with pip

Add --pre to the pip install options. Otherwise, prerelease versions are
not accepted by pip to resolve dependencies and problems appear when
building the venvs. For example tacker venv build fails with:

Could not find a version that satisfies the requirement neutron>=12.0.0

and we have neutron=13.0.0.0b3.dev94

Change-Id: I0dcb390a189b9fcad4dc5990b03c99ef30b4bbe4
Signed-off-by: Manuel Buil <mbuil@suse.com>
'}]
commit_message:
Consider prereleases when working with pip

Add --pre to the pip install options. Otherwise, prerelease versions are
not accepted by pip to resolve dependencies and problems appear when
building the venvs. For example tacker venv build fails with:

Could not find a version that satisfies the requirement neutron>=12.0.0

and we have neutron=13.0.0.0b3.dev94

Change-Id: I0dcb390a189b9fcad4dc5990b03c99ef30b4bbe4
Signed-off-by: Manuel Buil <mbuil@suse.com>

commit_message:
devstack: support lib/neutron

Support both legacy and current service naming in plugin
Use neutron_service_plugin_class_add function
Use new names in gate configuration
Remove config files from neutron-db-manage call

Also update CI configuration files location (we have them in tree now)

Change-Id: I76d13c6834d9da12fb372140f0c76758cbeb415d

commit_message:
Bind mount tripleo.cnf for tls everywhere work for telemetry

We need to bind mount the /var/lib/config-data/gnocchi/etc/my.cnf.d/tripleo.cnf.
for connections options to reflect in the gnocchi db sync
bootstrap container to work correctly. Also do the same for
ceilometer-agent-central so ceilometer_gnocchi_upgrade bootstrap
works properly with tls.

Change-Id: I363366b1698d9c03aec68623c35c6884ec961764

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-08-20 21:36:02.000000000', 'message': "Fix: Incorrect replication status on clusters

When running a replicated service in a cluster, the replication_status
field in the Cluster DB table doesn't get updated in some cases, making
the cluster look like it's non replicated:

- When starting a new clustered replicated service cluster.
- When enabling replication on an already clustered service.

The reason for that is that the service and cluster creation happens on
the Service's __init__ method, while the replication status isn't known
until later, when the start method in the service calls the manager's
init_host_with_rpc, where the manager updates the service DB entry.

This patch adds an update for the replication field to the cluster table
in that same place, making sure we have the right data.

Closes-Bug: #1758024
Change-Id: I0d2fded62372a2fc5f49538133c5b66694dccc77
(cherry picked from commit 43b1209f2a8accf7d2744da3c7a552e92d8a55be)
"}]
commit_message:
Fix: Incorrect replication status on clusters

When running a replicated service in a cluster, the replication_status
field in the Cluster DB table doesn't get updated in some cases, making
the cluster look like it's non replicated:

- When starting a new clustered replicated service cluster.
- When enabling replication on an already clustered service.

The reason for that is that the service and cluster creation happens on
the Service's __init__ method, while the replication status isn't known
until later, when the start method in the service calls the manager's
init_host_with_rpc, where the manager updates the service DB entry.

This patch adds an update for the replication field to the cluster table
in that same place, making sure we have the right data.

Closes-Bug: #1758024
Change-Id: I0d2fded62372a2fc5f49538133c5b66694dccc77
(cherry picked from commit 43b1209f2a8accf7d2744da3c7a552e92d8a55be)

commit_message:
Fix RDO builds

The RDO CI sets `%global skip_python3 1` which does not seem to do well
with py2pkg when py_versions only includes py3. Go back to building with
python2 and python3 so that the RDO builds work.

Change-Id: I99f0e55d34b6d117d4f58b05b7a461cda0404a1d

Once oslotest drops its dependency on testrepository, this package loses
it as a transitive dependency which causes it to start failing to build
with the error "ImportError: No module named 'anydbm'". This patch adds
python3-dbm as a build dependency so that oslotest can safely drop
testrepository.

subject: Revert "Fix automatic subnet CIDR generation"
messages:
[{'account_id': 23804, 'date': '2018-05-07 10:09:02.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 27329, 'date': '2018-05-08 07:28:36.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

Can you point out which tests are failing? The fix for those tests is probably quite simpler than reverting all this change.'}, {'account_id': 23804, 'date': '2018-05-08 07:35:30.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

> Can you point out which tests are failing? The fix for those tests
 > is probably quite simpler than reverting all this change.

Sure:
https://launchpad.net/bugs/1769609
https://launchpad.net/bugs/1766702'}, {'account_id': 27329, 'date': '2018-05-09 15:42:54.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

This things happen when creating bad implicit interfaces and not considering corner cases when refactoring (this is on me)

Now I understand your point and the regression I introduced.

The fix for it looks very simple.

1) Restore the default value for gateway parameter as before in method create_subnet
  gateway=''

2) In create_subnet method where gateway is assigned restore old behavior:
 
  if gateway is not None:
    kwargs['gateway_ip'] = str(gateway) or str(subnet_cidr.ip + 1)

3) Call it with parameter gateway=None in trunk test (as it was before).


In this way no gateway will be assigned when gateway is None as before."}, {'account_id': 11975, 'date': '2018-05-09 15:48:38.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

> This things happen when creating bad implicit interfaces and not
 > considering corner cases when refactoring (this is on me)
 > 
 > Now I understand your point and the regression I introduced.
 > 
 > The fix for it looks very simple.
 > 
 > 1) Restore the default value for gateway parameter as before in
 > method create_subnet
 > gateway=''
 > 
 > 2) In create_subnet method where gateway is assigned restore old
 > behavior:
 > 
 > if gateway is not None:
 > kwargs['gateway_ip'] = str(gateway) or str(subnet_cidr.ip + 1)
 > 
 > 3) Call it with parameter gateway=None in trunk test (as it was
 > before).
 > 
 > 
 > In this way no gateway will be assigned when gateway is None as
 > before.

Federico: I already proposed a patch to allow create subnet without gateway: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/566593/ - Please review if You can :)"}, {'account_id': 23804, 'date': '2018-08-24 10:19:28.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Revert "Fix automatic subnet CIDR generation"

This reverts commit 0ddc93b1b19922d08bedf331b57c363535bb357e.
This commit has broken trunk tests as described in bug 1769609. We
lost the ability to create a subnet without a gateway and this made
trunk tests to fail as the default route is overriden when fetching
the IP address of the subport disrupting the connectivity to the
guest VM FIP.

It also appears to be causing bug 1766702 so I'm proposing this revert
as it's not clear to me the exact issue that this commit is
addressing (it doesn't reference any bugs at all).

Change-Id: I87e162f86ba503d3ee53d1bf3dbe1c6923c76210
Closes-Bug: #1769609
Related-Bug: #1766702

I'd be keen on setting up a new job for rally against master (networking-ovn-rally-dsvm) to detect possible regressions in OVN. This should suffice along with the tempest job, what do you think? recheck'}, {'account_id': 6773, 'date': '2017-11-24 09:47:28.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2

I was a bit skeptical about changing defaults like that. I was thinking whether it would be better to keep it running against master so we could detect problems with the development of OVN faster (e.g performance degradation would be caught by rally). 

But after some thoughts I don't think networking-ovn should be the place for that. I believe that people using networking-ovn will and should run it against the released version of OVN. And, tests to OVN itself should be added there.

(That said, we still run tempest against master, which I would like to keep)

So I'm good with this. I still want other cores to weight on it, but leaving my vote here: +2!

Thanks Daniel"}, {'account_id': 23804, 'date': '2017-11-24 09:48:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Thanks guys for your reviews, I appreciate your comments'}, {'account_id': 10237, 'date': '2017-11-24 10:08:28.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Does this mean with devstack we will have ovs/ovn 2.8 ?

Can the version be selecting in the zuul job yaml files ?'}, {'account_id': 23804, 'date': '2017-11-24 10:15:22.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

> Does this mean with devstack we will have ovs/ovn 2.8 ?
 > 
Yes
 > Can the version be selecting in the zuul job yaml files ?

If the name of the job ends in "-master" then it'll checkout the master branch.'}, {'account_id': 10237, 'date': '2017-11-24 12:09:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

> > Does this mean with devstack we will have ovs/ovn 2.8 ?
 > >
 > Yes
 > > Can the version be selecting in the zuul job yaml files ?
 > 
 > If the name of the job ends in "-master" then it'll checkout the
 > master branch.

I personally prefer OVS master with devstack. I leave others to decide :).

Instead can we define the ovs branch (2.8, master etc) in the zuul job yaml file ?'}, {'account_id': 23458, 'date': '2017-11-24 13:28:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: -Code-Review

I'm sorry I canceled my vote because in gate.hook.sh the line related to environment variable of OVS is
"source $ NEUTRON_PATH/devstack/lib/ovs", so I think the changes  did not take effect to dsvm tests. Correct me if I am wrong.'}, {'account_id': 23804, 'date': '2017-11-27 10:19:11.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 23804, 'date': '2017-11-27 10:19:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

You're totally right!'}, {'account_id': 23804, 'date': '2017-11-27 11:07:13.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Published edit on patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 23804, 'date': '2017-11-27 11:31:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Published edit on patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 23804, 'date': '2017-11-27 13:16:55.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

(1 comment)

Thanks @Daniel.
We change the default OVS branch and it's in a non-configuration location, so could it be helpful to add some description to * local.conf.sample for the users to use master easily. As @Numan said, using master branch for a development environment is common use. Another comment is inline."}, {'account_id': 23804, 'date': '2017-11-28 12:25:57.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Thanks guys for reviewing. If we all agree to go ahead with master branch then I can abandon this patch'}, {'account_id': 6773, 'date': '2017-11-29 11:40:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

Thanks Daniel,

Some comments inline'}, {'account_id': 23458, 'date': '2017-12-01 03:38:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

@Daniel. I suggest add comment in * .local.conf.smaple to guide developers to modify master branch in their local devstack.
Aside from what you said, this patch has another benefit, we will  not need to modify ovs branches in code for new stable branch to adapt CI and this will reduce trivial further work.
Overall, I agree with this patch., thanks Daniel.'}, {'account_id': 23804, 'date': '2018-01-16 14:23:20.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 5.'}, {'account_id': 23804, 'date': '2018-01-16 14:32:53.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5:

(3 comments)'}, {'account_id': 23804, 'date': '2018-01-16 15:28:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6: Published edit on patch set 5.'}, {'account_id': 23804, 'date': '2018-01-16 16:39:32.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 6:

I think I can abandon this since I've verified that defining OVN_BRANCH=<branch/tag> it just works... What do you guys think?
The original intent of this patch was to not use master but as we agreed, we'll continue running against master branch so I can't see the value on this. Waiting for your inputs before abandoning it. 
Thanks!"}, {'account_id': 23804, 'date': '2018-01-16 16:39:37.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6: Workflow-1'}, {'account_id': 23804, 'date': '2018-08-24 10:19:15.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Ensure q-agt is not started if it is a disabled service

When using different neutron backends that do not require neutron
agent (q-agt), such as networking-odl, but still need some of the
q- services (such as q-dhcp or q-meta) the start_mutnauq_l2_agent
function at lib/neutron-legacy should not start q-agt if it is
specifically disabled. This patch include a checking similar to
the ones done at start_mutnauq_other_agents function.

Change-Id: Iba6748c8a5ab1cd0d95c980fe700f893dc565fb1

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-07-23 11:18:23.000000000', 'message': 'fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Change-Id: Idb45b993881084b4e19187cb09cead52dacf01bc
'}]
commit_message:
fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Change-Id: Idb45b993881084b4e19187cb09cead52dacf01bc

commit_message:
Remove support for devstack exercises

These seem to be not run for quite some time and they don't
succeed anymore - drop the code to avoid somebody accidentally
running it and wondering. A good example of "if it isn't tested
its broken".

Needed-By: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/581377/

commit_message:
Add testrepository dep to oslo.versionedobjects

oslotest has dropped its runtime dependency on testrepository[1] but
this package still relies on it, so add it as a build dependency until
it switches to stestr.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/569914

Change-Id: Icea4a84cada859fa2306a6c8116b783e5f26d17c

commit_message:
Release openstackdocstheme 1.23.1

This release is able to disable the badge automatically if a repo has no
stable branches. Also, disable the badge by default for releasenotes,
api-guide and api-ref.

Allow setting the storyboard project group to the name now.

Change-Id: I3d13653110105854f15a76ac97d3562ff8fd1a89

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: Ibcbc62c9004e4a33a4f9ce3046decfd076bf4f8f
Story: #2002586
Task: #24312

commit_message:
Drop tripleo-common-tempest-plugin deliverable

This repo exists, but the team does not actually have any tests in it,
so there is nothing really to release. Removing the deliverable for now
so it no longer shows up missing in our reports and does not get carried
forward to the next release cycle.

Change-Id: I3977aa00ab37a64ae320a94b774df7bc764bba68
Signed-off-by: Sean McGinnis <sean.mcginnis@gmail.com>
